---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Content Ecosystem" section="content-ecosystem">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">Channels & Budget · 90-Day Content Ecosystem</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">One story, every channel, <em>90 days.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">A research-backed, multi-channel plan — webinars, LinkedIn, podcasts, gated content, email, and paid — sequenced so each channel feeds the next. Built on real dental channels + benchmarks, not generic best-practice. The whole ecosystem exists to make one narrative impossible to miss.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>Build <strong>one flagship pillar asset per month</strong>, atomize it across every channel, and run all funnel stages at once (≈25% awareness / 40% proof / 35% convert). Your unfair head start: you <strong>already own the Becker's/Clerri survey of 105 dental leaders</strong> — that's the Month-1 benchmark report, ready now. SMB and DSO run as parallel tracks with different channels, unified by one monthly theme. Grounded in real research; sources at the bottom.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="content-ecosystem"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Pillar assets built: <span data-progress-here="content-ecosystem">0 / 0</span></p>

  <h2>The architecture — <em>one pillar feeds everything.</em></h2>
  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem">Don't create 50 disconnected posts. Build <strong>one flagship asset</strong>, then atomize it: a benchmark report becomes 8-15 ungated cluster blog posts (AEO-structured), a webinar, ~20 LinkedIn carousels/posts, founder ad creative, podcast talking points, and paid landing pages. One build, dozens of touches, one message.</p>
    <p style="margin:0"><strong>Run all stages simultaneously</strong> — TOFU/MOFU/BOFU compound only together. Each month advances the <em>theme</em>, not the funnel stage.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>The three waves <em>(months as themes).</em></h2>

  <h3>Month 1 · "The insurance escape is real" <span class="pill pill-mint">Awareness</span></h3>
  <div class="card wave">
    <p><strong>Pillar:</strong> the <strong>2026 Dental Membership Benchmark Report</strong> (built from the Becker's/Clerri survey you already own — 96% of leaders have 10-30% uninsured patients; 81% see cash-pay upside, only 19% capture it) + an interactive <strong>Practice Revenue-Leak / PPO Write-Off Calculator</strong>.</p>
    <p><strong>Atomizes into:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>SMB:</strong> founder/dentist starts posting on LinkedIn 3-5x/week ("fire your insurance company" POV); ungated AEO cluster posts; podcast-guesting outreach to <em>The Fee for Service Dentist Podcast</em>, <em>Dentalpreneur</em>, <em>Dentistry Uncensored</em>; high-intent paid search.</li>
      <li><strong>DSO:</strong> gate the benchmark report; LinkedIn Thought Leader Ads serving it; build the 50-100 named-account target list with sales; apply for Google HCP ad-targeting.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Month 2 · "Proof it works" <span class="pill pill-zest">Consideration</span></h3>
  <div class="card wave">
    <p><strong>Pillar:</strong> a <strong>customer-story webinar</strong> featuring a real practice + the written <strong>named-dentist case study</strong> (the "45→715 members, $1,575→$25,025 MRR in 24 months" kind of story — verify the actual customer).</p>
    <p><strong>Atomizes into:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>SMB:</strong> co-host an <strong>AADOM webinar</strong> for office managers ("cut insurance/claims admin with membership"); a Dentaltown thread; LinkedIn case-study + calculator ads; a sponsored <em>Dental Economics</em> / <em>Group Dentistry Now</em> piece.</li>
      <li><strong>DSO:</strong> co-host a <strong>GDN webinar</strong>; place an executive byline in <strong>Becker's</strong>; LinkedIn Document/Conversation ads serving peer DSO case studies segmented by persona (CFO / ops / marketing).</li>
      <li>Gate every webinar replay (≈45% of views come from on-demand).</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Month 3 · "Make the move" <span class="pill pill-wine">Conversion</span></h3>
  <div class="card wave">
    <p><strong>Pillar:</strong> conversion assets — the <strong>DIY-vs-Clerri compliance guide</strong> (neutralizes the real competitor) + <strong>CFO ROI one-pagers</strong> + demo offers.</p>
    <p><strong>Atomizes into:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>SMB:</strong> LinkedIn single-image + Lead-Gen Form ads to retargeted/calculator audiences; paid search to demo/pricing pages; the 5-email nurture (from the <a href="/clerri/messaging-playbook">Messaging Playbook</a>) drives to demo.</li>
      <li><strong>DSO:</strong> sequence 8+ ABM touches into target accounts ahead of <strong>ADSO/DIA Mid-Winter (Mar)</strong> and <strong>DEO Summit (Apr-May)</strong>; book on-site exec meetings; CFO ROI one-pagers as the closing asset.</li>
      <li>Refresh the pillar page for AEO (beat the ~13-week citation decay).</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>Channel playbooks <em>(real benchmarks).</em></h2>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
  <table class="ctable">
    <thead><tr><th>Channel</th><th>The play</th><th>Benchmark / rule</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><strong>Webinars</strong></td><td>Educational + customer-story + panel beat demos. Co-host with GDN (DSO) + AADOM (office managers). Always gate the replay.</td><td>Plan 35-45% reg→attend; 35-45 min beats 60; ~1/week, Thursdays; ~45% of views are on-demand.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>LinkedIn (organic)</strong></td><td>Founder/exec-led, not company page. Document/carousel + story-driven posts. 3-5x/week.</td><td>Personal profiles ~8x company-page engagement; exec posts 3-6% vs ~1.8%.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>LinkedIn (paid)</strong></td><td>Thought Leader Ads (boost founder posts) for reach; single-image + Lead-Gen Forms for BOFU capture.</td><td>TLA 2.68% CTR vs 0.42% (6.4x), $2.29 vs $13.23 CPC; B2B CPL ~$310 paid.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Podcasts</strong></td><td>Guesting &gt; owning. Pick by buyer proximity, not audience size. Account-based: invite DSO leaders as guests.</td><td>~10 appearances/quarter; account-based podcasting ~10%+ guest→pipeline. Attribute in CRM.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Gated content</strong></td><td>Gate only high-value MOFU/BOFU (calculator, benchmark report). Keep TOFU + an HTML summary of every gated PDF ungated for SEO/AEO.</td><td>Interactive calculator ~8.3% vs static PDF ~3.8% (directional).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>SEO / AEO</strong></td><td>Front-load a 2-3 sentence answer per section; question-format H2/H3; sequential headings; FAQ/HowTo/Org schema.</td><td>~44% of AI citations come from the page opening; sequential headings ~2.8x citation odds; refresh quarterly (13-week decay).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Paid search</strong></td><td>High-intent dental keywords → demo/pricing LPs. Apply for Google HCP targeting; health is a "sensitive category" (no condition targeting).</td><td>Dental CPC ~$7.85, CTR 5.44%, CVR 9.08%, CPL ~$84 (optimized $30-50). DSO CPL $400-600+.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Email</strong></td><td>The written SMB nurture + patient-education + renewal lifecycle (in-house, off 7knots templates). See Messaging Playbook.</td><td>Trigger on calculator/report download; informational for patient track (compliance).</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  </div>

  <h2>The flagship assets to build <em>(in order).</em></h2>
  <div data-section="content-ecosystem"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="ce-01-benchmark" data-section="content-ecosystem" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">2026 Dental Membership Benchmark Report — repackage the Becker's/Clerri survey (you own the data)</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="content-ecosystem"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="ce-02-calculator" data-section="content-ecosystem" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Interactive Revenue-Leak / PPO Write-Off Calculator (the #1 lead magnet — calculators ~2x static PDFs)</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="content-ecosystem"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="ce-03-casestudy" data-section="content-ecosystem" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Named-customer case study (the MRR-growth story) — verify the customer + numbers</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="content-ecosystem"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="ce-04-diyguide" data-section="content-ecosystem" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">DIY-vs-Clerri compliance-risk guide (neutralizes the real competitor)</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="content-ecosystem"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="ce-05-cfo" data-section="content-ecosystem" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">CFO ROI one-pager (CFOs drive ~80% of DSO decisions)</div></div></label></div>

  <h2>Segment routing <em>(who hears what, where).</em></h2>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
  <table class="ctable">
    <thead><tr><th>Segment</th><th>Message</th><th>Primary channels</th><th>Anchor asset</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><strong>Owner-dentist</strong></td><td>Freedom + economics</td><td>Podcasts (Fee for Service, Dentalpreneur), Dentaltown, LinkedIn, paid search</td><td>Write-off calculator + MRR case study</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Office manager</strong></td><td>Less admin, fewer denials, hours back</td><td>AADOM (webinars, OBSERVER, Insurance Symposium)</td><td>"Hours-saved" admin webinar + checklist</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>DSO committee</strong></td><td>EBITDA / predictable revenue / standardized rollout (per role)</td><td>Becker's, GDN, LinkedIn, ADSO/DEO events, ABM</td><td>Benchmark report + CFO ROI one-pager + peer case studies</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Patients</strong></td><td>Informational only (anti-kickback)</td><td>Practice-deployable email + the directory</td><td>"What membership covers" set (see <a href="/clerri/patient-acquisition">Patient Acquisition</a>)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Measurement</h2>
  <div class="callout mint">
    <p style="margin:0">Run multi-touch attribution from day one (last-touch lies in a 8+ touchpoint, committee motion). Track: pillar-asset downloads, webinar reg→attend→demo, podcast guest→pipeline, content-sourced pipeline (once the SF→HubSpot deal-sync lands), and per-segment cost-per-lead vs. the dental benchmarks above. Measure pipeline, not clicks.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Where to start</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:70ch"><strong>This week:</strong> commission the Benchmark Report from the Becker's survey data (your fastest pillar — the data exists) + start the founder LinkedIn cadence (free, immediate). <strong>Next:</strong> the calculator (the lead magnet everything else feeds) + book the first podcast guest spots. Everything connects to the <a href="/clerri/messaging-playbook">Messaging Playbook</a> (copy), <a href="/clerri/content-bank">Content Bank</a> (ideas), and <a href="/clerri/patient-acquisition">Patient Acquisition</a> (the member leg).</p>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">Ecosystem notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="content-ecosystem-notes" placeholder="What's converting per channel, webinar/podcast booking status, calculator performance, attribution learnings..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--muted);margin-top:1.5rem">Research-grounded (Jun 2026): Goldcast/ON24/MarketingProfs (webinars), ZenABM/Impactable (LinkedIn), WordStream/LocaliQ/PPCChief (dental paid), Frase/BlogSEO (AEO), Omniscient/Fame (podcasts), Becker's/Group Dentistry Now/ADSO/DEO/AADOM/Dentaltown (dental channels), Kleer/Veritas (SMB economics). Some benchmarks are directional (single-source) — flagged in the research notes. Verify customer stats before publishing.</p>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/messaging-playbook"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">Messaging Playbook</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/content-bank"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">Content Bank</span></a>
  </div>

</div>

